## <a id='components'></a> Sink Resources

In <%= vars.product_short %>, you can deploy log sinks and metric sinks to
monitor your Kubernetes nodes and workloads.

To deploy a log or a metric sink:

1. Enable sink resources in the <%= vars.product_tile %> tile following the
instructions above.
1. Create sink resources. For instructions, see
[Creating Sink Resources](create-sinks.html).

For conceptual information about
sink resources, see:

* [Overview](create-sinks.html#overview) in _Creating Sink Resources_
* [Sink Architecture in <%= vars.product_short %>](sink-architecture.html)

Also see:

* [Monitoring Clusters with Log Sinks](monitor-sinks.html)

## <a id='integrations'></a> Supported Integrations

<%= vars.product_short %> supports the following integrations:

* **Wavefront**. For more information, see
[VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid Integration Details](https://docs.wavefront.com/integrations_pks.html)
in the Wavefront documentation.
  <p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> You can also create a metric sink
  to send metrics to Wavefront.</p>
* **cAdvisor**. For more information, see
[cAdvisor](https://github.com/google/cadvisor) on GitHub and
[VMware vRealize Operations Management Pack for Container Monitoring](https://docs.vmware.com/en/Management-Packs-for-vRealize-Operations-Manager/1.4/container-monitoring/GUID-BD6B5510-4A16-412D-B5AD-43F74C300C91.html)
in the VMware documentation.
